<a href=http://www.legacyofsorrow.net/site/news.php3>Legacy of Sorrow</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaauminki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aauminki</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 276<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/01 3:19:10 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SoL: Combat Stability (Damage Mitigation)</span><hr size=1> Based purely on the fact that mobs still hit for up to their normal max, I'd say that it's the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> chance</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to mitigate damage that is correct. <p><big><center>
