<br>
<a href=http://www.legacyofsorrow.net/site/news.php3>Legacy of Sorrow</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ueviscerosheadcutter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evisceros Headcutter</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/01 3:36:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SoL: Combat Stability (Damage Mitigation)</span><hr size=1> My guess is that damage mitigation is a skill check like any other.  So IF you successfully mitigate damage, then the damage is reduced by 2, 5, or 10%.  I have absolutely no backing for this, but hey, it sure sounds good, eh?   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7657" target="_blank">Evisceros Headcutter</a><BR>
<a href="http://thedarkexile.homestead.com/" target="_blank">The Dark Exile</a> <BR> Warlord of the 7th Hammer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaauminki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aauminki</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 280<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/01 3:40:48 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SoL: Combat Stability (Damage Mitigation)</span><hr size=1> Could be, but having a 2% chance of reducing the damage 2% doesn't make much sense to me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usinark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinark</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/01 10:38:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SoL: Combat Stability (Damage Mitigation)</span><hr size=1> My guess is that 2% is added to your AC in the middle of some whacky calculation, and that whole thing is then rolled against the mob's attack which is so much bigger that mitigation will make absolutely no difference whatsoever =P<br>
<br>
In other words, if you think the AC cap is 1250, then there's a good chance you'll think mitigation is worthless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umablesirrup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MableSirrup</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/01 11:03:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SoL: Combat Stability (Damage Mitigation)</span><hr size=1> Mitigation seems to be working from the other end.  Mobs can still hit for max damage, but their minimum damage is decreased.  We were fighting frogloks in Seb that were hitting those of us with no mitigation for a minimum of 30 while the one member that had mitigation (one or two points, not sure) was getting hit for 28 minimum.<br>
<br>
If this is how it truly works, then the effect seems to be of questionable worth on high end encounters.  How often do uber mobs hit for minimum damage afterall? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usolosstormreaper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solos Stormreaper</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://hellra1ser.homestead.com/files/Ring.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 2:23:07 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hellra1ser.homestead.com/files/Darkstar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SoL: Combat Stability (Damage Mitigation)</span><hr size=1> The people who say it has a chance to mitigate damage may be right.  It certainly doesn't work like defensive where every hit is reduced by 2%.  I tested it out, thinking it would be like defensive, but as you can see in this shot, the mob hit for max (I sat down to get hit for max) before and after for the same amount. 2% of 92 is 1.84.<br>
<br>
